    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Genesis",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 2,
        "summary": "The Creation is completed\u2014God rests on the seventh day\u2014The prior spirit creation is explained\u2014Adam and Eve are placed in the Garden of Eden\u2014They are forbidden to eat of the tree of knowledge of good and evil\u2014Adam names every living creature\u2014Adam and Eve are married by the Lord.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Thus the heavens and the earth were finished, and all the host of them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Creation.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 45:12; D&C 29:36; 38:1; 45:1; Moses 3:1; Abr. 5:1.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And on the seventh day God ended his work which he had made; and he rested on the seventh day from all his work which he had made.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0done.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0stopped, ceased; from the verb shavat; the noun shabbat (Engl. Sabbath) means a stopping or cessation. D&C 77:12; Moses 3:2 (1\u20133); Abr. 5:2 (1\u20133). TG\u00a0Rest.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Industry.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And God blessed the seventh day, and sanctified it: because that in it he had rested from all his work which God created and made.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sabbath.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 20:11; Mosiah 13:19 (16\u201319); D&C 77:12; Moses 3:3 (1\u20133); Abr. 5:3 (1\u20133). TG\u00a0Sacred.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 31:17.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0created through working.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "These are the generations of the heavens and of the earth when they were created, in the day that the Lord God made the earth and the heavens,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 3:4 (4\u20135); Abr. 5:4 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the Lord God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Nature, Earth.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Spirit Creation.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Creation.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, Physical Creation of.",
                        "start": 180,
                        "end": 183
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 3:5.",
                        "start": 196,
                        "end": 202
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 164,
                        "end": 173
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But there went up a mist from the earth, and watered the whole face of the ground.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0(also) flood, flow.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord God formed man of the dust of the ground, and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living soul.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, Physical Creation of.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Creation.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 18:27; Morm. 9:17; D&C 77:12; 93:35 (33\u201335); Moses 3:7; 4:25 (25\u201329); 6:59; Abr. 5:7.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:26; D&C 77:2; 93:33; Abr. 5:7 (7\u20138). TG\u00a0Breath of Life.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 104
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Adam.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 113
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 88:15. TG\u00a0Soul.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord God planted a garden eastward in Eden; and there he put the man whom he had formed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Eden.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And out of the ground made the Lord God to grow every tree that is pleasant to the sight, and good for food; the tree of life also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of knowledge of good and evil.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sight.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 3:9; Abr. 5:9. TG\u00a0Food.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 107
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 3:24; Rev. 2:7; 22:2 (2, 14); 1\u00a0Ne. 8:10 (10\u201312); 11:25 (21\u201322, 25); 15:36 (22, 28, 36); 2\u00a0Ne. 2:15; Alma 12:26 (21, 23, 26); 32:40; 42:5 (2\u20136); Moses 3:9; 4:28 (28, 31); Abr. 5:9.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 117
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Immortality.",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 125
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge; Opposition.",
                        "start": 175,
                        "end": 184
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And a river went out of Eden to water the garden; and from thence it was parted, and became into four heads.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Eden.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0divided into four heads (branches).",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The name of the first is Pison: that is it which compasseth the whole land of Havilah, where there is gold;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0encircles.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 10:29 (7, 29); 25:18; Moses 3:11.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 4
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the gold of that land is good: there is bdellium and the onyx stone.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0lapis lazuli, or cornelian (identity uncertain).",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the name of the second river is Gihon: the same is it that compasseth the whole land of Ethiopia.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0encircles.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0Cush. Moses 3:13.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the name of the third river is Hiddekel: that is it which goeth toward the east of Assyria. And the fourth river is Euphrates.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord God took the man, and put him into the garden of Eden to dress it and to keep it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Purpose of.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Eden.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0to till it.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:41.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord God commanded the man, saying, Of every tree of the garden thou mayest freely eat:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Commandments of God.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Agency.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil, thou shalt not eat of it: for in the day that thou eatest thereof thou shalt surely die.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 3:3; 2\u00a0Ne. 2:15.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Abr. 5:13.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 3:17. TG\u00a0Death; Death, Spiritual, First; Fall of Man; Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn; Mortality.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord God said, It is not good that the man should be alone; I will make him an help meet for him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 3:18; Abr. 5:14. TG\u00a0Marriage, Celestial.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0a helper suited to, worthy of, or corresponding to him. Moses 3:18; Abr. 5:14. TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And out of the ground the Lord God formed every beast of the field, and every fowl of the air; and brought them unto Adam to see what he would call them: and whatsoever Adam called every living creature, that was the name thereof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:34; 3:19; Abr. 1:3; 5:20.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 121
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Language.",
                        "start": 217,
                        "end": 221
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 111
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 209,
                        "end": 212
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Adam gave names to all cattle, and to the fowl of the air, and to every beast of the field; but for Adam there was not found an help meet for him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord God caused a deep sleep to fall upon Adam, and he slept: and he took one of his ribs, and closed up the flesh instead thereof;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the rib, which the Lord God had taken from man, made he a woman, and brought her unto the man.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, Physical Creation of.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Adam said, This is now bone of my bones, and flesh of my flesh: she shall be called Woman, because she was taken out of Man.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 29:14; Jacob 2:21; Moses 3:23; Abr. 5:17.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Creation; Woman.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore shall a man leave his father and his mother, and shall cleave unto his wife: and they shall be one flesh.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Husbands.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Fatherhood.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:22; 49:15 (15\u201316); Moses 3:24 (23\u201324); Abr. 5:18 (17\u201318). TG\u00a0Chastity.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 13:24; Alma 44:5; 3\u00a0Ne. 18:21. TG\u00a0Family, Patriarchal; Marriage, Wives.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Divorce; Family, Eternal; Marriage, Celestial; Marriage, Marry; Unity.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they were both naked, the man and his wife, and were not ashamed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 3:7; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:14; Moses 4:13 (13, 16\u201317).",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}